    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 20</em>, <em>PRPG Core Rulebook pg. 143</em></p><h3><span title=\"PFS Legal\">[PFS]</span> Statistics</h3><p><strong>Cost</strong> 50 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 12 lbs.</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d6/1d4 (small), 1d8/1d6 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> x3; <strong>Range</strong> -; <strong>Type</strong> P or S; <strong>Special</strong> brace, double</p><p><strong>Category</strong> Two-Handed; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Exotic</p><p><strong>Weapon Groups</strong> Double</p><h3>Description</h3><p>A dwarven urgrosh is a double weapon- an axe head and a spear point on opposite ends of a long haft. The urgrosh's axe head is a slashing weapon that deals 1d8 points of damage. Its spear head is a piercing weapon that deals 1d6 points of damage. You can use either head as the primary weapon; the other becomes the off-hand weapon. If you use an urgrosh against a charging character, the spear head is the part of the weapon that deals damage. Dwarves treat dwarven urgroshes as martial weapons.</p>"
